ue\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 30, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104exh1665703229141.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/exh1665703229141.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/exh1665703229141.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"exh1665703229141\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">$IOPRINT\n  </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify the types of messages sent to the message frame or log file.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"exh1665703229141__topic_d140708e1_d140709e1_d140710e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exh1665703229141__p_d140711e1_d140712e1_d140713e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$IOPRINT</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">MessageLevel</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exh1665703229141__section_pqh_h5x_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d986788e66\">Arguments</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exh1665703229141__p_d140717e1_d140718e1_d140719e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">MessageLevel</var>—integer representing\n        the sum of the message codes for the desired message types. If the sum of the codes is\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>, no information is placed in the message frame. For more information,\n        see the \"I/O Message Levels\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exh1665703229141__section_dn5_h5x_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d986788e80\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exh1665703229141__p_d140723e1_d140724e1_d140725e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$IOPRINT</span> determines the types\n        of messages that will appear in the message frame. You can use the ProcScript function\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ioprint</span> to test or change the current I/O message level.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exh1665703229141__p_d140726e1_d140727e1_d140728e1\">This setting only takes effect after the assignment\n        file has been read and overrides the value set by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pri</span>, which is applied\n        immediately upon startup.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exh1665703229141__section_hfy_l5x_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d986788e101\">Example: Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$IOPRINT</span></h2>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"exh1665703229141__pre_kvd_45x_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[SETTINGS]\n$IOPRINT = 63</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exh1665703229141__p_d140732e1_d140733e1_d140734e1\">63 is the sum of all message codes up to and including\n        Generated SQL (if available). Therefore, the message frame returns all messages for codes 1,\n        2, 4, 8, 16 and 32.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kyc1665702707205.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$ioprint</a><p>Return or set the message level in the message frame.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/unz1665702549564.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/pri</a><p>Specify the types of messages sent to the message frame or log file.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nqh1665702549702.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>I/O Message Levels</a><p>Most of the messages that display in the message frame are determined by the I/O message level. The I/O message is a number that is determined by adding up the codes of the applicable message types.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rlu1665702707277.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Runtime Messages and Log Files</a><p>All Uniface applications can be configured to create log files that collect runtime messages generated during the application session. The messages may be generated by ProcScript commands in your application, or by Uniface to document actions, events, warnings and errors. You can configure which Uniface runtime messages are reported.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527378\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527378\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$IOPRINT Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 30, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $IOPRINT Specify the types of messages sent to the message frame or log file. $IOPRINT = MessageLevel Arguments MessageLevel —integer representing the sum of the message codes for the desired message types. If the sum of the codes is 0 , no information is placed in the message frame. For more information, see the \"I/O Message Levels\" topic. Description The $IOPRINT determines the types of messages that will appear in the message frame. You can use the ProcScript function $ioprint to test or change the current I/O message level. This setting only takes effect after the assignment file has been read and overrides the value set by /pri , which is applied immediately upon startup. Example: Setting $IOPRINT [SETTINGS] $IOPRINT = 63 Copy 63 is the sum of all message codes up to and including Generated SQL (if available). Therefore, the message frame returns all messages for codes 1, 2, 4, 8, 16 and 32. Related Links $ioprint Return or set the message level in the message frame. /pri Specify the types of messages sent to the message frame or log file. I/O Message Levels Most of the messages that display in the message frame are determined by the I/O message level. The I/O message is a number that is determined by adding up the codes of the applicable message types. Runtime Messages and Log Files All Uniface applications can be configured to create log files that collect runtime messages generated during the application session. The messages may be generated by ProcScript commands in your application, or by Uniface to document actions, events, warnings and errors. You can configure which Uniface runtime messages are reported. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}